capsfilter.author: David Schleef <ds@schleef.org>
capsfilter.description: Pass data without modification, limiting formats

caps.blurb: Restrict the possible allowed capabilities (NULL means ANY). Setting this property takes a reference to the supplied GstCaps object.

ts-offset.blurb: Timestamp offset in nanoseconds for synchronisation, negative for earlier sync

adjust-base.blurb: Adjust the base value of segments to ensure they are adjacent

high-percent.blurb: High threshold for buffering to finish. Emits GST_MESSAGE_BUFFERING with a value of 100%%

low-percent.blurb: Low threshold for buffering to start. Emits GST_MESSAGE_BUFFERING with a value of 0%%

max-size-bytes.blurb: Max. amount of data to buffer (bytes, 0=disable)

max-size-time.blurb: Max. amount of data to buffer (in ns, 0=disable)

temp-location.blurb: Location to store temporary files in (Only read this property, use temp-template to configure the name template)

temp-template.blurb: File template to store temporary files in, should contain directory and XXXXXX. (NULL == disabled)

fakesink.author: Erik Walthinsen <omega@cse.ogi.edu>, Wim Taymans <wim@fluendo.com>, Mr. 'frag-me-more' Vanderwingo <wingo@fluendo.com>

drop-out-of-segment.blurb: Drop and don't render / hand off out-of-segment buffers

num-buffers.blurb: Number of buffers to accept going EOS

signal-handoffs.blurb: Send a signal before unreffing the buffer

datarate.blurb: Timestamps buffers with number of bytes per second (0 = none)

filltype.blurb: How to fill the buffer, if at all

format.blurb: The format of the segment events

is-live.blurb: True if the element cannot produce data in PAUSED

parentsize.blurb: Size of parent buffer for sub-buffered allocation

signal-handoffs.blurb: Send a signal before pushing the buffer

sync.blurb: Sync to the clock to the datarate

fdsink.author: Erik Walthinsen <omega@cse.ogi.edu>
fdsink.description: Write data to a file descriptor

fd.blurb: An open file descriptor to write to
An open file descriptor to read from

timeout.blurb: Post a message after timeout microseconds (0 = disabled)

filesink.author: Thomas Vander Stichele <thomas at apestaart dot org>

append.blurb: Append to an already existing file

buffer-size.blurb: Size of buffer in number of bytes for line or full buffer-mode

location.blurb: Location of the file to write

max-transient-error-timeout.blurb: Retry up to this many ms on transient errors (currently EACCES)

o-sync.blurb: Open the file with O_SYNC for enabling synchronous IO

filesrc.author: Erik Walthinsen <omega@cse.ogi.edu>
filesrc.description: Read from arbitrary point in a file

location.blurb: Location of the file to read

forward-sticky-events.blurb: Forward sticky events on stream changes

check-imperfect-offset.blurb: Send element messages if offset and offset_end do not match up

check-imperfect-timestamp.blurb: Send element messages if timestamps and durations do not match up

datarate.blurb: (Re)timestamps buffers with number of bytes per second (0 = inactive)

drop-buffer-flags.blurb: Drop buffers with the given flags

drop-probability.blurb: The Probability a buffer is dropped

signal-handoffs.blurb: Send a signal before pushing the buffer

single-segment.blurb: Timestamp buffers and eat segments so as to appear as one segment

ts-offset.blurb: Timestamp offset in nanoseconds for synchronisation, negative for earlier sync

input-selector.author: Julien Moutte <julien@moutte.net>, Jan Schmidt <thaytan@mad.scientist.com>, Wim Taymans <wim.taymans@gmail.com>

sync-streams.blurb: Synchronize inactive streams to the running time of the active stream or to the current clock

extra-size-buffers.blurb: Amount of buffers the queues can grow if one of them is empty (0=disable) (NOT IMPLEMENTED)

extra-size-bytes.blurb: Amount of data the queues can grow if one of them is empty (bytes, 0=disable) (NOT IMPLEMENTED)

extra-size-time.blurb: Amount of time the queues can grow if one of them is empty (in ns, 0=disable) (NOT IMPLEMENTED)

high-percent.blurb: High threshold for buffering to finish. Only used if use-buffering is True (Deprecated: use high-watermark instead)

high-watermark.blurb: High threshold for buffering to finish. Only used if use-buffering is True

low-percent.blurb: Low threshold for buffering to start. Only used if use-buffering is True (Deprecated: use low-watermark instead)

low-watermark.blurb: Low threshold for buffering to start. Only used if use-buffering is True

max-size-buffers.blurb: Max. number of buffers in the queue (0=disable)

max-size-bytes.blurb: Max. amount of data in the queue (bytes, 0=disable)

max-size-time.blurb: Max. amount of data in the queue (in ns, 0=disable)

min-interleave-time.blurb: Minimum extra buffering for deinterleaving (size of the queues) when use-interleave=true

sync-by-running-time.blurb: Synchronize deactivated or not-linked streams by running time

unlinked-cache-time.blurb: Extra buffering in time for unlinked streams (if 'sync-by-running-time')

use-buffering.blurb: Emit GST_MESSAGE_BUFFERING based on low-/high-percent thresholds (0%% = low-watermark, 100%% = high-watermark)

use-interleave.blurb: Adjust time limits based on input interleave

pad-negotiation-mode.blurb: The mode to be used for pad negotiation

resend-latest.blurb: Resend latest buffer after a switch to a new pad

current-level-buffers.blurb: Current number of buffers in the queue

current-level-bytes.blurb: Current amount of data in the queue (bytes)

current-level-time.blurb: Current amount of data in the queue (in ns)

flush-on-eos.blurb: Discard all data in the queue when an EOS event is received

leaky.blurb: Where the queue leaks, if at all

max-size-buffers.blurb: Max. number of buffers in the queue (0=disable)

max-size-bytes.blurb: Max. amount of data in the queue (bytes, 0=disable)

max-size-time.blurb: Max. amount of data in the queue (in ns, 0=disable)

min-threshold-buffers.blurb: Min. number of buffers in the queue to allow reading (0=disable)

min-threshold-bytes.blurb: Min. amount of data in the queue to allow reading (bytes, 0=disable)

min-threshold-time.blurb: Min. amount of data in the queue to allow reading (in ns, 0=disable)

bitrate.blurb: Conversion value between data size and time

current-level-buffers.blurb: Current number of buffers in the queue

current-level-bytes.blurb: Current amount of data in the queue (bytes)

current-level-time.blurb: Current amount of data in the queue (in ns)

high-percent.blurb: High threshold for buffering to finish. Only used if use-buffering is True (Deprecated: use high-watermark instead)

high-watermark.blurb: High threshold for buffering to finish. Only used if use-buffering is True

low-percent.blurb: Low threshold for buffering to start. Only used if use-buffering is True (Deprecated: use low-watermark instead)

low-watermark.blurb: Low threshold for buffering to start. Only used if use-buffering is True

max-size-buffers.blurb: Max. number of buffers in the queue (0=disable)

max-size-bytes.blurb: Max. amount of data in the queue (bytes, 0=disable)

max-size-time.blurb: Max. amount of data in the queue (in ns, 0=disable)

ring-buffer-max-size.blurb: Max. amount of data in the ring buffer (bytes, 0 = disabled)

temp-location.blurb: Location to store temporary files in (Only read this property, use temp-template to configure the name template)

temp-template.blurb: File template to store temporary files in, should contain directory and XXXXXX. (NULL == disabled)

use-bitrate-query.blurb: Use a bitrate from a downstream query to estimate buffer duration if not provided

use-buffering.blurb: Emit GST_MESSAGE_BUFFERING based on low-/high-percent thresholds (0%% = low-watermark, 100%% = high-watermark)

use-rate-estimate.blurb: Estimate the bitrate of the stream to calculate time level

use-tags-bitrate.blurb: Use a bitrate from upstream tags to estimate buffer duration if not provided

alloc-pad.blurb: The pad ALLOCATION queries will be proxied to (DEPRECATED, has no effect)

allow-not-linked.blurb: Return GST_FLOW_OK even if there are no source pads or they are all unlinked

has-chain.blurb: If the element can operate in push mode

pull-mode.blurb: Behavior of tee in pull mode

typefind.author: Benjamin Otte <in7y118@public.uni-hamburg.de>
typefind.description: Finds the media type of a stream

force-caps.blurb: force caps without doing a typefind

minimum.blurb: minimum probability required to accept caps

valve.author: Olivier Crete <olivier.crete@collabora.co.uk>
valve.description: Drops buffers and events or lets them through

drop.blurb: Whether to drop buffers and events or let them through
